Register Tenstorrent-WH-BlockSpMM with the host tt-metal build.

Adds a single add_subdirectory() call to tt-metal's programming_examples
CMakeLists.txt so the submodule's CMake participates in the parent build.

Apply from $TT_METAL_HOME (the root of your tt-metal checkout) with:
    patch -p1 < tt_metal/programming_examples/Tenstorrent-WH-BlockSpMM/host_integration/programming_examples.patch

Baseline: tt-metal tag v0.63.0.

--- a/tt_metal/programming_examples/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/tt_metal/programming_examples/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -8,6 +8,7 @@
 add_subdirectory(${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/profiler)
 add_subdirectory(${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/distributed)
 add_subdirectory(${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/contributed)
+add_subdirectory(${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/Tenstorrent-WH-BlockSpMM)

 add_subdirectory(${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/add_2_integers_in_compute)
 add_subdirectory(${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/add_2_integers_in_riscv)
